The course provides theoretical and practical knowledge about pathological diagnostics of surgical, oncological and internal diseases, required for independent work as a general practitioner. The sources of theoretical knowledge are the textbooks and presentations, video lectures and self-assessment tests represented in the Moodle learning platform. For learning of microscopic alterations, the database of digital microscopy slides with tutorial videos is available in the Moodle, grouped according to the topics. In the seminars, discussions of independently learned materials takes place and drawing associations with clinical significance.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of clinical pathology course I is to provide deeper theoretical and practical knowledge about surgical pathology and pathology of internal medicine in accordance with the program of IV year. The aim is to provide an understanding of the causes, nature and diagnosis of diseases using morphological methods (microscopic examination of tissue samples, cells and body fluids), interpreting of histological diagnosis and integrating this into comprehensive medical reasoning. In addition, the aim is to provide understanding of proper sampling (biopsies and cytological material).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who graduated the course getting at least the minimal grade: knows principles of tissue sampling,  knows the causes and pathogenesis of diseases, is able to understand the meaning of histological diagnoses, understands the most important morphological changes of diseases, and as a result is capable of apply this knowledge in daily medical practice.
